post.description:
Loads assets by a given collection of pair <b>&lt;assetId, versionNumber&gt;</b> and a loadMask. The loadMask is used
to load the requested external properties of the AssetRestDto. The returned response contains 2 collections.
The first collection <code>assets</code> contains all assets which are found and are contained in the request.
The second collection <code>statuses</code> contains status objects for each not-found asset and asset resource version.
If the client does not provide <b>versionNumber</b> for any if the requested assets, the response will contains an entry
with the requested asset and its latest version.
<p>
Maximum 200 assets can be requested via this endpoint. If you request more than 200 assets a BAD_REQUEST response will be returned.
<p>
If any of the given arguments - assetId or versionNumber is missing, BAD_REQUEST is returned as this is invalid request.
<p>
<p>
If the load mask is omitted, the response will contains the found assets with no loaded relations to them, ie. no variants or themes.

expandable (String, Optional) vdb,license,language,variants,countries,customProperties,persons,
downloadApproval,themes,watchers,relations,freeFields,structuredKeywords,uploadApproval,
division,channelPublications,owner,customAttributes

</p>
For example if we pass the following collection, where the asset with id 74568 has only 2 versions with numbers (0 and 1),
and the asset 52353 doesn't exist at all, the response will contains 2 items in the assets collections representing each version
of the 74568 asset, and 2 items in statuses collection, which represents the not-existing version 2 of 74568 asset, and the not existing
asset with id 52353 with version 0:
<br>
Request:
<pre>
